## Description
## 
The **Transfer invoices (EI) **task allows to send a package of electronic invoices to the EI service, where the invoices in the package are processed, validated, sent to SdI and LEA following the Account and Company configuration as well as the invoice configuration.

> Important

This feature is only available on Milan tenants.

## Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

## Input
The expected input of the **Transfer invoices (EI) **task is the following:

- a group of electronic invoices in XML format with the SdI filename (for example: *IT012345678901_00001.xml*)

- a manifest file for each electronic invoice with the same name as the invoice, containing all invoice-related information, in JSON or XML format; for example:

JSON format: *IT012345678901_00001.json*

- XML format: *IT012345678901_00001.manifest*

> Note

Invoices can be renamed using the [Rename Invoices (EI)](/doxee-platform/docs/rename-invoices-ei-batch-workflow-task-reference) task.

It is not necessary to sign invoices in the Batch Workflow, as they can be signed directly in the Electronic Invoicing service using the JSON configuration or the Company configuration.

> Important

In order to avoid performance and technical issues when sending electronic invoices, the invoices to be processed by this task should not exceed 10000 units for each task iteration.

> Warning

BOTH BP task use similar fields (which have the same meaning describe inside the table on bottom), but they have a different XML and JSON VALIDATION, In xml structure "tag field" with empty value is not admitted for number and date data.

```## Output
No output is produced in Batch Workflows.

An EI package is created in the Electronic Invoicing service, containing the XML invoice files, the corresponding JSON metadata files and a *MANIFE ST.json *file with detailed package information (such as job, input and lot ID).

### EI package specifications
The EI package is a ZIP file containing the following files:

- XML invoice files

- JSON metadata files

- *MANIFEST.json*

#### Naming convention
`EI.{{DATE}}.{{JOB}}.{{LOT}}.zip`**Field**

**Value**

**EI**

Fixed value

**DATE**

Creation date of the ZIP file (format: yyyyMMddHHmmss)

**JOB**

Job ID

**LOT**

Lot ID

For example: *EI.20220919230743.134135711.0000100232311643.zip*

> Important

In order to avoid performance and technical issues, each task iteration should not contain more than 10000 XML invoices (and their corresponding JSON metadata files).

### Sample *MANIFEST.json *file
`{
"workUnit": "file.zip", "workUnitHash": "sdjfksfjksfhsf", "workUnitReceptionDate": "", "sourceApplication": "MyApplicaiton", "jobId": "12345",
"lotID": "112223423434",
"scope": "TEST",
"account": "TBD", "invoiceNumber": 11
}`#### Fields
**Field**

**Corresponding DP3 Field**

**Notes**

**workUnit**

Input file name

**workUnitHash**

Input file hash

**workUnitReceptionDate**

*Currently not present on DP3.*

Date format: yyyy-MM-dd'T'hh:mm:ss.SSS+0000

**sourceApplication**

Application name

**jobId**

Job ID

**lotId**

Lot ID

**scope**

**TEST **for INTEGRATION tenants

**PRODUCTION **for PRODUCTION tenants

**account**

*Currently not present on DP3.*

**invoiceNumber**

*Currently not present on DP3.*

Number of invoices in input

#### Fields
**Field**

**Description**

**Notes**

**filename**

XML invoice filename

System variable *$InputFileName*

**filesize**

Size of the XML

System variable *$InputFileSize*

**invoiceCount**

Progressive number of the invoice within the XML

This value should be set to "1".

**signProfile**

Signing profile

DP3 signing profile code

> Note

If this value is not set, the sign profile configured for the company is used. If the company sign profile is not set, the account is used.

**toApprove**

Option to indicate that the invoice needs to be approved before it can be sent to the SdI

Possible values:

- **true **(requires approval in the Documents service's UI)

- **false **(no approval required)

> Note

If this value is not set, the default value is "false".

**invoices[x]. type**

Document type

*FatturaElettronica.FatturaElettronicaHeader.DatiTrasmissione.FormatoTrasmissione*

**invoices[x]. shipmentId**

Shipment ID saved on Tracking &amp; Reporting

GUID operator

**invoices[x]. invoiceNumber**

Invoice number

*FatturaElettronica.FatturaElettronicaBody.DatiGenerali.DatiGeneraliDocumento.Numero*

**invoices[x]. invoiceDate**

Invoice date

*FatturaElettronica.FatturaElettronicaBody.DatiGenerali.DatiGeneraliDocumento.Data*

(format: YYYY-MM-DD)

**invoices[x]. invoiceAmount**

Invoice amount (including tax)

*FatturaElettronica.FatturaElettronicaBody.DatiGenerali.DatiGeneraliDocumento. ImportoTotaleDocumento*

**invoices[x]. recipientCode**

Invoice receiver name, code, or business name

The value depends on the application.

(usually: the "Denominazione" of the "CessionarioCommittente" (the receiver) of the invoice or another identifier)

**invoices[x]. company**

DP3 Company

Exact name of the Company configured during the set up of the Electronic Invoicing service

**invoices[x]. division**

Division

The value depends on the application.

(for example: the Company name or the specific division of the invoice, "Sezionale")

**invoices[x]. taxable**

Invoice amount (without tax)

The value depends on the application.

(usually: the sum of *FatturaElettronica.FatturaElettronicaBody.DatiBeniServizi. DatiRiepilogo.ImponibileImporto *only if *FatturaElettronica.FatturaElettronicaBody. DatiBeniServizi.DatiRiepilogo.AliquotaIVA *is different from 0)

**invoices[x]. dueDate**

Invoice due date

The value depends on the application.

**invoices[x]. splitPayment**

Esigibilit IVA

The value depends on the application.

(usually: *FatturaElettronicaBody.DatiBeniServizi.DatiRiepilogo.EsigibilitaIVA*)

**invoices[x]. internalClient Code**

Customer code

Depending on the application. It could be the Customer code of the invoice

**invoices[x]. paymentExecu torCode**

Payment executor code

The value depends on the application.

**invoices[x]. accountingSe ctor**

Accounting sector

The value depends on the application.

**invoices[x]. userName**

User who created the invoice

The value depends on the application.

**invoices[x]. leaMetadata. k00 - k14**

K index field value configuration on LEA

> Important

It must be exact value configuration used on LEA.

The value depends on the application.

**invoices[x]. leaMetadata. companyCode**

Legal entity on LEA

> Important

It must be the exact value of the company code on LEA.

**invoices[x]. leaMetadata. documentType**

Document type on LEA

> Important

It must be the exact "TipoDocumento" used on LEA.

**invoices[x]. leaMetadata. source**

Source on LEA

**invoices[x]. leaMetadata. description**

Description on LEA

**invoices[x]. leaMetadata. directory**

LEA directory

Usually an empty string

**invoices[x]. leaMetadata. pages**

Number of pages

For electronic invoices, the value is "1".

**invoices[x]. customFields**

Additional custom fields needed for the reports

Example:

`"field1": "value1",
"field2": "value2", 
"field3": "value3"`
